vi and Vim Editors Pocket Reference

introduction
This pocket reference is a companion to Learning the vi and vim Editors, by Arnold Robbins et al, It describes the vi
 com-mand-line options, command-mode  commands, ex com- mands and options, regular expressions and the use of the 
substitues (s) commands, and other pertinent information for using vi.

While retanining coverage of the bi clones, nvi, elvis, and vile, this edition offers expanded coverage if the Vim editor,which has become the de facto standard version of vi in the GNU/Lunux world.

The Solaris version of vi served as trhe "referend" version of the original vi for this pocket reference.

Convemtions
The following font conventions are used in this book:
courier
    Used for filenames, command names, options, and every-thing to be typed literlly.

courier Italic
    Used for repalceable text within commands.
Italic
     Used for replaceable text within regular text, Internet URLs,for emphasis,and for new terms when first defined 
[...]
    Identidies optional text; the bravkets are not typed.
[CTRL-G]
   indicates a keystroke.

